analysisPopulations.name: Intent-to-Treat Population
analysisPopulations.text: The ITT population includes all subjects who are randomized. This population will be used for the primary efficacy analysis and all other efficacy analyses, unless otherwise specified.
analysisPopulations.label: ITT
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The ITT population includes all subjects who are randomized. This population will be used for the primary efficacy analysis and all other efficacy analyses, unless otherwise specified.

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Analysis Set includes all randomized subjects who received at least one dose of any study treatment (ibrutinib/placebo, bendamustine, or rituximab).
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Analysis Set includes all randomized subjects who received at least one dose of any study treatment (ibrutinib/placebo, bendamustine, or rituximab).
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose of any study treatment

analysisPopulations.name: Per-Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.text: The per-protocol set is a subset of the ITT population, excluding subjects with major protocol deviations that may impact the primary efficacy endpoint. The specific criteria for exclusion will be finalized prior to database lock.
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The per-protocol set is a subset of the ITT population, excluding subjects with major protocol deviations that may impact the primary efficacy endpoint. The specific criteria for exclusion will be finalized prior to database lock.
analysisPopulations.criteria: ITT population AND no major protocol deviations

analysisPopulations.name: PK Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The PK analysis set includes all subjects who received at least one dose of ibrutinib and have at least one evaluable PK sample.
analysisPopulations.label: PK
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The PK analysis set includes all subjects who received at least one dose of ibrutinib and have at least one evaluable PK sample.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received >=1 dose of ibrutinib AND >=1 evaluable PK sample

characteristics.name: sMIPI score
characteristics.description: Simplified MCL international prognostic index score (low risk [0-3] vs. intermediate risk [4-5] vs. high risk [6-11])

characteristics.name: TP53 Mutation Status
characteristics.description: Presence or absence of TP53 mutation
